{"word":"σχέθω","slug":"σχέθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σχέθω</b></el> <el>(Σχέθω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <el>ἔχω</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>*<a href='S:σχέθω'><el>σχέθω</el></a> assumed as a <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hold</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>simply <i>to have</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to hold back, keep away</i> or <i>off</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>αἷμα ἔσχεθον</el> <i>staunched</i> the blood, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}